\n}}\n{{see also|2019 Notre Dame Fighting Irish football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegeSecondaryHeader|team=Virginia Tech Hokies|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n|1\u20131\n|Oct. 6, [[2018 Virginia Tech Hokies football team|2018]]\n|'''L''', 23\u201345\n|}\nAfter poor performances against USC and Michigan, Notre Dame stepped up defensively against Virginia Tech.  The hokies were held to their lowest total yards game since 2015 and lowest yards per play since 2016 in what was billed as \"one of the best group effort performances\" ever seen by [[Sports Illustrated]] sportswriter Bryan Driskell.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/college/notredame/football/notre-dame-football-grades-defense-virginia-tech|publisher=[[Sports Illustrated]]|accessdate=November 6, 2019|title=Grades: Notre Dame Defense vs. Virginia Tech|first=Bryan|last=Driskell|date=November 4, 2019}}</ref>  Yet, Notre Dame still needed a late touchdown to win the game by a final score 21-20 and Notre Dame extended their home winning streak to 16 games.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/ncaaf/2019/11/02/notre-dame-beats-virginia-tech-ian-book-touchdown-final-minute/4143938002/|publisher=[[USA Today]]|first=Mike|last=Berardino|date=November 2, 2019|accessdate=November 6, 2019|title=No. 16 Notre Dame needs late touchdown to get past Virginia Tech}}</ref>\n\n===Wake Forest===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=No. 22 Demon Deacons\n|R1=3 |R2=7 |R3=7 |R4=0\n|Home='''Hokies'''\n|H1=3 |H2=3 |H3=17|H4=13\n}}\n{{see also|2019 Wake Forest Demon Deacons football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Virginia Tech Hokies|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n|24\u201312\u20131\n|Nov. 22, [[2014 Virginia Tech Hokies football team|2014]]\n|'''L''', 3\u20136\n|}\n\n===at Georgia Tech===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road='''Hokies'''\n|R1=14|R2=17|R3=14|R4=0\n|Home=Yellow Jackets\n|H1=0 |H2=0 |H3=0 |H4=0\n}}\n{{see also|2019 Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegeSecondaryHeader|team=Virginia Tech Hokies|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n|9\u20137\n|Oct. 25, [[2018 Virginia Tech Hokies football team|2018]]\n|'''L''', 28\u201349\n|}\n\n===Pittsburgh===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=Panthers\n|R1=0 |R2=0 |R3=0 |R4=0\n|Home='''Hokies'''\n|H1=14 |H2=7 |H3=0 |H4=7\n}}\n{{see also|2019 Pittsburgh Panthers football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Virginia Tech Hokies|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n|10\u20138\n|Nov. 10, [[2018 Virginia Tech Hokies football team|2018]]\n|'''L''', 22\u201352\n|}\n\n===at Virginia===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=No. 24 Hokies\n|R1=3 |R2=3 |R3=21|R4=3\n|Home='''Cavaliers'''\n|H1=13|H2=0 |H3=7 |H4=19\n}}\n{{see also|2019 Virginia Cavaliers football team}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegeSecondaryHeader|team=Virginia Tech Hokies|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n|58\u201337\u20135\n|Nov. 23, [[2018 Virginia Tech Hokies football team|2018]]\n|'''W''', 34\u201331\n|}\n\n===vs Kentucky (Belk Bowl)===\n{{Linescore Amfootball|\n|Road=Hokies\n|R1=10|R2=7|R3=10|R4=3\n|Home='''Wildcats'''\n|H1=7|H2=7|H3=10|H4=13\n}}\n{{see also|2019 Kentucky Wildcats football team|2019 Belk Bowl}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Virginia Tech Hokies|Overall record|Last meeting|Result}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n|6\u201311\u20132\n|Oct. 31, [[1987 Virginia Tech Hokies football team|1987]]\n|'''L''', 7\u201314\n|}\n\n== Honorary #25 Beamer Jersey ==\nSince the start of the 2016 season, during the week before each game, Head Coach [[Justin Fuente]] selects an outstanding player to wear the #25 jersey in honor of former head coach, [[Frank Beamer]], who wore #25 as a player for Virginia Tech. The jersey reprepsents hard work, toughness, good sportsmanship and being a exemplary teammate. At first, the distinction was intended strictly for special teams players, but has since been expanded to include all team members.\n\nThe players honored in the 2019 season are:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hokiesports.com/news/2019/12/29/football-brian-johnson-to-wear-beamer-no-25-jersey-for-belk-bowl.aspx|title=Brian Johnson to wear Beamer No. 25 jersey for Belk Bowl|website=Virginia Tech Athletics|language=en|access-date=2019-12-29}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Game\n!Opponent\n!Player(s)\n|-\n|Game 1\n|Boston College\n|Tyree Rodgers\n|-\n|Game 2\n|Old Dominion\n|Divine Deablo (2)\n|-\n|Game 3\n|Furman\n|Dylan Rivers\n|-\n|Game 4\n|Duke\n|Oscar Bradburn (3)\n|-\n|Game 5\n|Miami\n|Jarrod Hewitt\n|-\n|Game 6\n|Rhode Island\n|<dfn>Devon Hunter</dfn> \n|-\n|Game 7\n|North Carolina\n|<dfn>Rayshard Ashby</dfn> \n|-\n|Game 8\n|Notre Dame\n|Armani Chatman\n|-\n|Game 9\n|Wake Forest\n|Divine Deablo (3)\n|-\n|Game 10\n|Georgia Tech\n|<dfn>Khalil Ladler</dfn> (2)\n|-\n|Game 11\n|Pittsburgh\n|<dfn>James Mitchell</dfn> \n|-\n|Game 12\n|Virginia\n|[[Dalton Keene]] (2) & Rayshard Ashby (2)\n|-\n|Belk Bowl\n|Kentucky\n|<dfn>Brian Johnson</dfn>\u00a0 \u00a0\n|-\n|}\n\n== Rankings ==\n{{Further|2019 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings}}\n{{NCAA Division I FBS CFP ranking movements\n| year            = {{2019}}\n| finalpollweek   = 16\n| cfpfirstweek    = 10\n| AP_pre          = RV\n| coaches_pre     = RV\n| AP_1            = NR\n| coaches_1       = NR\n| AP_2            = NR\n| coaches_2       = NR\n| AP_3            = NR\n| coaches_3       = NR\n| AP_4            = NR\n| coaches_4       = NR\n| AP_5            = NR\n| coaches_5       = NR\n| AP_6            = NR\n| coaches_6       = NR\n| AP_7            = NR\n| coaches_7       = NR\n| AP_8            = NR\n| coaches_8       = RV\n| AP_9            = RV\n| coaches_9       = RV\n| cfp_9           = NR\n| AP_10           = RV\n| coaches_10      = RV\n| cfp_10          = NR\n| AP_11           = RV\n| coaches_11      = RV\n| cfp_11          = NR\n| AP_12           = 