n==\n===Preseason media poll===\nIn the preseason ACC media poll, Virginia Tech was predicted to finish in third in the Coastal Division.<ref>{{cite web|title=Clemson Favored to Continue ACC Football Championship Run|url=http://theacc.com/news/2019/7/22/clemson-favored-to-continue-acc-football-championship-run.aspx|website=theACC.com|publisher=Atlantic Coast Conference|date=July 22, 2019|accessdate=July 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"display: inline-table;\"\n|align=\"center\" Colspan=\"3\" |'''Media poll (Coastal Division)'''\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Virginia Tech Hokies|Predicted finish|Team|Votes (1st place)}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 1 || Virginia || 1003 (82)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 2 || Miami (FL) || 992 (55)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 3 || '''Virginia Tech''' || 827 (20)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 4 || Pittsburgh || 691 (8)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 5 || Duke || 566 (6)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 6 || North Carolina || 463 (1)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 7 || Georgia Tech || 302 (1)\n|}\n\n==Schedule==\nIn non-conference play, Virginia Tech played home games against [[2019 Old Dominion Monarchs football team|Old Dominion]] of [[Conference USA]], [[2019 Furman Paladins football team|Furman]] of the [[Southern Conference]], and [[2019 Rhode Island Rams football team|Rhode Island]] of the [[Colonial Athletic Association]], as well as a road game against [[2019 Notre Dame Fighting Irish football team|Notre Dame]], a [[NCAA Division I FBS independent schools|football independent]]. In [[Atlantic Coast Conference|ACC]] play, the Hokies will play the other members of the Coastal Division as well as [[2019 Boston College Eagles football team|Boston College]] and [[2019 Wake Forest Demon Deacons football team|Wake Forest]] from the Atlantic Division.\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 2019\n| poll = [[2019 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings#AP Poll|AP Poll]] and [[2019 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings#CFP Rankings|CFP Rankings]] after N