\n| title14         = [[Save Me (Queen song)|Save Me]]\n| length14        = 3:48\n| title15         = [[Don't Stop Me Now]]\n| length15        = 3:34\n| title16         = [[Good Old-Fashioned Lover Boy]]\n| length16        = 2:55\n| title17         = [[I Want to Break Free]]\n| length17        = 4:22\n| note17          = single mix, from ''[[The Works (Queen album)|The Works]]'', 1984\n| writer17        = Deacon\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed       = yes\n| headline        = 2004 US edition (''Greatest Hits: We Will Rock You'')<br />{{nobold|Same track listing as UK 1981 edition, followed by three additional tracks.}}\n| total_length    = 69:17\n| title18         = [[I'm in Love with My Car]]\n| note18          = rare original single mix, from ''A Night at the Opera'', 1975\n| writer18        = [[Roger Taylor (Queen drummer)|Roger Taylor]]\n| length18        = 3:12\n| title19         = Under Pressure\n| note19          = from ''[[Queen on Fire \u2013 Live at the Bowl]]'', 2004\n| length19        = 3:39\n| title20         = [[Tie Your Mother Down]]\n| note20          = from ''Queen on Fire \u2013 Live at the Bowl'', 2004\n| writer20        = May\n| length20        = 3:52\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed       = yes\n| headline        = 2011 Japan reissue edition<br />{{nobold|From the bonus track for Japan, available on iTunes.}}\n| total_length    = 63:00\n| title18         = [[Teo Torriatte (Let Us Cling Together)]]\n| note18          = From ''A Day at the Races'', 1976\n| writer18        = May\n| length18        = 5:07\n}}\n\nIn addition to the variations above, the official biography ''Queen: As It Began'' by Jacky Gunn and Jim Jenkins states the following variations on the original UK track listing:{{citation needed|date=April 2015}}\n\n*Argentina, Brazil, Mexico and Venezuela had \"Love of My Life\" (live version) instead of \"Seven Seas of Rhye\".\n*Belgium and Spain had \"Spread Your Wings\" as an extra track.\n*Australia was identical to the US version, but had \"Tie Your Mother Down\" as an extra track.\n*Bulgaria had \"Death On Two Legs\" and \"Sweet Lady\" as extra tracks.\n*Canada, France, Germany, Israel and Netherlands had \"Under Pressure\" as an extra track.\n*Germany also added \"Spread Your Wings\" on some first pressing copies.\n\n==Personnel==\n* [[Freddie Mercury]] \u2013 lead, backing and [[Opera#operatic voices|operatic vocals]], acoustic piano, [[Tack piano|jangle piano]], fingersnaps, bicycle bells, handclaps, acoustic guitar, organ, synthesizer, footstomps, fingersnaps (on original North American release only), drum machine (on 1991 North American release only), [[synth bass]]\n* [[Brian May]] \u2013 acoustic and electric guitars, co-lead vocals on \"Fat Bottomed Girls\" (chorus), backing and operatic vocals, bicycle bells, handclaps, piano, synthesizer, footstomps, fingersnaps (on original North American release only), co-lead vocals on \"Keep Yourself Alive\" (bridge), [[harmonium]] (on Japanese release only)\n* [[Roger Taylor (Queen drummer)|Roger Taylor]] \u2013 acoustic and (on 1991 North American release only) electronic drums, percussion, backing and operatic vocals, [[timpani]], gong, triangle, chimes, bicycle bells, handclaps, woodblocks, tambourine, footstomps, fingersnaps (on original North American release only), cowbell, co-lead vocals on \"Keep Yourself Alive\" (bridge), rhythm guitar (on 2004 US edition)\n* [[John Deacon]] \u2013 bass guitar, electric guitar, acoustic and electric pianos, bicycle bells, handclaps, footstomps, fingersnaps (on original North American release only), synthesizer (on 1991 North American release only)\n\n;Additional personnel (original UK release)\n* [[Mike Stone (record producer)|Mike Stone]] \u2013 co-lead vocals on \"Good Old-Fashioned Lover Boy\"\n* [[Roy Thomas Baker]] \u2013 [[stylophone]] on \"Seven Seas of Rhye\"\n\n;Additional personnel (original North American release)\n* [[David Bowie]] \u2013 co-lead vocals on \"Under Pressure\"\n\n;Additional personnel (1991 North American release)\n* [[Fred Mandel]] \u2013 synthesizer on \"I Want to Break Free\"\n\n== Charts ==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" |Chart (1981\u201382)\n!scope=\"col\" |Peak<br />position\n|-\n|align=\"left\" |Australian Albums ([[Kent Music Report]])<ref name=\"auchart\">{{Cite book |title=Australian Chart Book 1970\u20131992 |last=Kent |first=David |authorlink=David Kent (historian) |publisher=Australian Chart Book |location=[[St Ives, New South Wales]], Australia |page=243 |date=1993 |isbn=0-646-11917-6}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n|-\n{{album chart|Austria|1|artist=Queen|album=Greatest Hits}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Netherlands|1|artist=Queen|album=Greatest Hits}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Germany4|1|artist=Queen|album=Greatest Hits|id=1358}}\n|-\n{{album chart|New Zealand|1|artist=Queen|album=Greatest Hits}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Norway|21|artist=Queen|album=Greatest Hits}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UK|1|artist=Queen|id=21275|refname=\"UKchart\"}}\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" |Chart (1992)\n!scope=\"col\" |Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|8|artist=Queen|album=Greatest Hits}}\n|-\n|Canadian Top Albums<ref>{{cite journal |date=17 October 1992 |title=100 Albums (CD's & Cassettes) |journal=[[RPM (magazine)|RPM]] |volume=56 |issue=16 |format=PHP/PDF |issn=0315-5994 |accessdate=25 July 2011 |url=http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.1904&type=2&interval=50&PHPSESSID=m89iq841abagb37ld9c0fdc1f3 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023212049/http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/rpm/028020-119.01-e.php?&file_num=nlc008388.1904&type=2&interval=50&PHPSESSID=m89iq841abagb37ld9c0fdc1f3 |archive-date=23 October 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|4\n|-\n|French Compilations<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.infodisc.fr/Albums_ChartRun.php |title=Les \"Charts Runs\" de chaque Album Class\u00e9 |wor